  title: What is the difference between `performed`, `started`, and `canceled` in
    input actions?
  text: 'These are events tied to action lifecycles.

    - `started`: When the input
    begins (like pressing down a key)

    - `performed`: When the input is considered
    "activated"

    - `canceled`: When the input ends (key released)

    But for
    continuous movement, you usually just check `.IsPressed()` every frame instead
    of using events.'
